As for the taste, I personally don't kick, the texture of the meatballs is good but the taste seems less savory. That's my personal opinion, but salt and flavoring are provided at the table for buyers who want to make their own (Original) Warung bakso yang berlokasi di depan Superindo Banyumanik. Untuk pelengkapnya hanya ada krupuk, saos, sambal, kecap. Pilihan minuman ada fresh tea, le minerale, dan standar es teh, es jeruk. Pelayanan cepat. Untuk rasa kalau saya pribadi kurang nendang, tekstur baksonya baik tapi rasa seperti kurang gurih. name: inggar putri
review: (Translated by Google) Do you know the boxed meatballs when I bought them here in high school in 2008. The prices are cheap with large portions. The noodles are not stingy at all. In a bowl, you get 1 box of meatballs (large meatballs cut into squares), 1 quail egg meatball, 2 muscle meatballs, 1 meatball tofu. But here I'm changing meatballs because I don't really like tofu and I use white corn noodles instead of so'un. That's the type of broth, not the clear, fresh one, because the boxed meatballs have a mixture like that, which if you get hot sauce, it turns into oil, I don't know what it's called. Recommend hot oranges to drink. First, because the gravy is oily so the oranges are fresher, secondly because they haven't used ice crystals so it's better if you cough easily, and thirdly because the iced tea isn't that good. A portion of meatballs + iced tea = just 18k I like the small meatballs compared to the box meatballs and the quail egg meatballs. It's more meaty and chewy, for some reason. (Original) Kenal bakso kotak ya pas beli disini jaman smp tahun 2008. Harganya murah dengan porsi yang banyak. Mienya pun nggak pelit sama sekali. Semangkuk dapat 1 bakso kotak (bakso besar dipotong2 kotak), 1 bakso telur puyuh, 2 bakso urat, 1 tahu bakso. Tapi disini aku ganti bakso karena emang nggak begitu doyan tahu yaa dan pake mie putih jagung bukan so'un. Tipe kuah kaldu gitu yaa, bukan yang bening segar karena bakso kotaknya itu ada campuran gitu yang kalo kena kuah panas jadi minyak gitu, apa namanya nggak tahu. Rekomen jeruk panas untuk minumnya. Pertama karena kuah berminyak jadi kalo jeruk lebih segar, kedua karena belum pake es kristal jadi mending anget aja kalo kalian gampang batuk, dan ketiga karena es teh nya ngga terlalu enak sih. Seporsi bakso + es teh = 18k aja Aku suka bakso kecil2nya dibanding bakso kotak sama bakso telur puyuhnya. Lebih kerasa dagingnya dan kenyal sih, entah kenapa. Parking: Limited parking

review: Yes this is the best bakso you could find around Banyumanik and Tembalang area in Semarang. The place is not too cozy but it hides plentyful authenticity of Bakso. To reach this place easily you need Google maps direction.

name: Muhammad Afif
review: Ey ey, The best bakso (Indonesian Meatballs) in upper semarang city. Affordable price with serious taste. The solid round of beef and starch mixture bring tremendous pleasure. Chewiness and great aroma will bring you here again and again. You can order bakso-es in a great bakso, also tendon-dissolved meatballs or "Bakso Urat" and adding floating quasi-solid tallow in your bowl. Finally, iced tea and orange juice will quench your thirst . Very hungry? add lontong or double your noodle. Feel something to crunch? there are also different type of kerupuk here. Wanna add famous acar and sambal, just add as you want to. You will find no wifi here, just bakso and iced tea in great summer will bring your greatest indonesian experience. Classical small scale bakso vendor with hospitable owner, friendly server, also safety-aware parking lot helper. 5/5

name: Regina FY
review: (Translated by Google) Try this Baso at night, the location is next to the transmart near the intersection. Ask the father, it is open from 12.30 to 21.00, the price of the Baso is IDR 19,000 per serving. How does it feel? Yummy The bass is bouncy, supple, solid, not soft when you bite it. The gravy is hot too. The sambal is spicy Then earlier, we were making dinner so we beat the rice too. The rice is delicious too, fluffier, clean white. There are ready to swallow/offal too, just because it was finished, it's not there anymore. You can choose vermicelli or yellow noodles too. On the table there is a choice of fried tofu as well as snacks to eat with the baso. Overall it's delicious, if you go to Semarang again, this will be on the list of Must-Try Foods (Original) Nyobain Baso ini pas kulineran malem, lokasi di samping transmart deket simpang lima itu. Nanya si bapak nya buka dari jam 12.30 sampai jam 21.00, Harga Baso nya IDR 19,000 per porsi. Rasa nya gimana ? Enakkk Baso nya mantul, kenyel, padet, gak gembos gt digigit. Kuah nya juga panas. Sambel nya pedessss Trus tadi kita-kita kan buat makan malem jadi hajar nasi juga. Nasi nya enak juga, pulen, putih bersih. Ada sedia tetelan/jeroan juga, cuma krn tadi penghabisan, uda gak ada. Bisa pilih bihun atau mie kuning juga. Di meja ada pilihan tahu goreng juga buat cemal cemil makan sama si baso. Overall enak, klo ke Semarang lagi, ini bakal masuk list Makanan Wajib Coba

review: (Translated by Google) The meatball subscription tastes good with a fresh gravy. Most like to request using tetelan + tofu. The standard portion price is not too expensive. If you come here at peak hours, you have to be patient in line to get a seat. But how come the masons there are helping to find an empty seat. Service is fast and ok. (Original) Bakso langganan rasanya enak dengan kuah yang segar. Paling suka request pakai tetelan + tahu. Harga seporsinya standar nggak terlalu mahal. Kalau ke sini pas jam ramai, harus sabar antre dapat tempat duduk. Tapi dibantu kok sama mas-mas di sana untuk cari kursi kosong. Pelayanan cepat dan ok.

name: fransiska29
review: (Translated by Google) champion!! the place is just not comfortable, especially if it's hot during the day queuing (Original) juara!! tempatnya aja krg nyaman apalagi kalo siang2 panas ngantri

name: andre santoso
review: (Translated by Google) One of the most famous beef meatballs in Semarang. The location is on the side of the seroja road before the Telogorejo Hospital. The meatballs here are delicious, the meat tastes good and the gravy is solid. There are also offal and meat options. The service is fast, the cleanliness of the street stalls is standard, the price is quite affordable. (Original) Salah satu bakso sapi yang cukup terkenal di Semarang. Lokasinya ada di pinggir jalan seroja sebelum RS Telogorejo. Baksonya disini enak, dagingnya terasa dan kuahnya mantap. Ada juga pilihan jerohan dan daging. Pelayanannya cepat, kebersihan standard warung kaki lima, harganya cukup terjangkau.

name: Ilham restu Kartiko
review: (Translated by Google) Highly recommended because of the delicious taste of the meatballs and offal, right to eat when it rains (Original) Sangat recommended dikarenakan rasa baso dan daging jeroannya yang lezat, pas disantap saat hujan

name: Hana Novita
review: (Translated by Google) The taste is good, the meatball gravy is thick but it doesn't make you feel nauseous. The stuffing of the innards is not stingy (Original) Rasa enak, kuah baksonya kental tapi tidak bikin eneg. Isian jeroan nya tidak pelit

name: Dee Dee
review: (Translated by Google) Savory & chewy beef meatballs that fit perfectly plus delicious tripe, if you like to use rice, it's also available. Open from 13.00 to 21.00 (but if it runs out then you can close immediately) (Original) Bakso sapi yg gurih & kenyal yg pas mantap ditambah babat yg maknyus, kalau yg suka pakai nasi juga tersedia. Buka mulai jam 13.00 s.d 21.00 (tapi kalau sudah habis maka bisa segera tutup)
